---
title: Rump Steak with Chimichurri, Potato Wedges and Stir-Fried Runner Beans
description: Here at HelloFresh, we love a bit of chimichurri. It's a word that rolls easily off the tongue for a sauce that tastes great on it. Although chimichurri comes from Argentina (where it's particularly popular with steak) the name has Basque origins. It means something like 'a bunch of things in no particular order'. We think you'll agree that when a combination is as delicious as this, the sequence really isn't important!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/rump-steak-wk34-5f89e9bc.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/rump-steak-wk34-51b59b59.pdf
